# Dependencies — never committed; bundles ship with everything inlined
node_modules/
web/node_modules/

# Build caches / TypeScript intermediates
.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Runtime state (lives in user's home, not in repo)
.comark/

# NOTE: bundled outputs ARE committed so the plugin install works without
# requiring users to run `npm install`:
#   - web/dist/     (Vite bundle of the SPA)
#   - server/dist/  (esbuild bundle of the HTTP server + deps)
#   - mcp/dist/     (esbuild bundle of the MCP server + deps)
#
# Regenerate all three with: npm run build
#
# The user-facing gitignore template (what users add to THEIR project):
#   *.comark.json
#   .comark/
# Documented in README and INSTALL.md.
